    <help><![CDATA[
        IRMA (Iterative Refinement Meta-Assembler) can be used to obtain robust assembly, variant calling, and phasing of highly variable RNA viruses. 
        These are obtained after an iterative assembly approach. For more information visit https://wonder.cdc.gov/amd/flu/irma/
        IRMA is deployed with modules for influenza, ebolavirus and coronavirus. This galaxy wrapper currently only supports influenza modules.

        Just specify the module and provide your read data. For advanced users more settings are available in the advanced config section.
        Warning: Settings of the advanced config section you edit, may override settings from the selected module configuration. The defaults may not be the module defaults, but global defaults of IRMA.
    ]]></help>
